sentences: Audun Ellingsen (born 4 January 1979) is a Norwegian jazz musician (Upright bass) known from collaborations within bands like "Sphinx" and with musicians like Frøy Aagre, Erlend Slettevoll and Gisle Torvik.
Jazz came to be the main musical focus when he went to the musical program at high school in 1998, and he picked up the double bass.

After graduation he attended musical studies at Toneheim Folkehøgskole for one year, followed by studies on the jazzprogram at Leeds College of Music (1999) under guidance of Stuart Riley and Zoltan Dekaney.
Ellingsen took a Bachelor of Arts in Jazz Studies and got a Masters of Music degree in 2004.
